text: Coffee taste and quantity is really good. Worth the money. But I feel other food items are over priced. I feel tarts could be better in terms of taste also.

A tiny cafe tucked off the corner @ Science Park II, a good place if you need a ME-time!
My first visit today & here I eat to my heart's content!
A gem in science park! Particularly impressed by the egg tart. Enjoyed my weekend breakfast here thoroughly. Will definitely come again.

ice coffee was super diluted for me. saw them make my coffee only pour half of the metal tin, then add water. after all that into a cup of ice.... so overall, i think it's roughly 70-80% water for 4.20? never coming back again
Suitable for breakfast and lunch.  The inside of the store is not large, so it is best to avoid crowded times.
